HEADWORD: Bough
<hw>Bough</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>bogh</ets>,
AS. <ets>b⟦omac⟧g</ets>, <ets>b⟦omac⟧h</ets>, bough, shoulder; akin to
Icel. <ets>b⟦omac⟧gr</ets> shoulder, bow of a ship, Sw. <ets>bog</ets>,
Dan. <ets>bov</ets>, OHG. <ets>buog</ets>, G. <ets>bug</ets>, and to
Gr.<?/ ( for <?/ ) forearm, Skr. <ets>b⟦amac⟧hu</ets> (for
<ets>bh⟦amac⟧ghu</ets>) arm. ⟦root⟧88, 251. Cf. <er>Bow</er> of a
ship.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>An arm or branch of a tree, esp. a large arm or main
branch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A gallows.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>boughless</ent>⟦br⟧
